item.title: CVE-2022-1605|2024-08-03T00:10:03.598Z -- unknown -- email%20users
item.description: The Email Users WordPress plugin through 4.8.8 does not have CSRF check in place when updating its settings, which could allow attackers to make a logged in admin change them via a CSRF attack and change the notification settings of arbitrary users
